  <static seed="74" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring100.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{24x^{5}y^{10}-16x^{4}y^{10}+16x^{3}y^{10}}=</m> <fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8x^{3}y^{10}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}-2x+2\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>8x^3y^{10}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{24x^{5}y^{10}-16x^{4}y^{10}+16x^{3}y^{10}}={8x^{3}y^{10}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}-2x+2\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
